<% content_for :page_title, "Pass.js" %>
<% content_for :page_description, "Pass.js tracks referral traffic. It helps analyze conversion funnels by capturing URL parameters through hidden form fields. It’s very small and easy to install." %>
<div class="col-md-12 col-lg-10 offset-lg-1 mt-12">
	<div class="row mb-5">
		<div class="col-sm-6">
			<h2><strong><%= yield :page_title %></strong></h2>
			<p>Pass.js tracks referral traffic. It helps analyze conversion funnels by capturing URL parameters through hidden form fields. It’s very small and easy to install.</p>
		</div>
	</div>

	<div class="row mb-6">
		<div class="col-sm-6">
			<h5 class="mb-3">The Challenge</h3>
			<p>While at Fathom, clients often asked how many leads could be attributed to their PPC campagin. These values needed to be tracked to better understand where leads were coming from.</p>
		</div>
		<div class="col-sm-6">
			<h5 class="mb-3">The Outcome</h3>
			<p>A reusable javascript library that accurately tracks leads. Weighing only 3 kilobytes, Pass.js can be used with little overhead.</p>
		</div>
	</div>
		
	
	<hr class="sm mb-8"/>
	
	<div class="row mb-8">
		<div class="col-xs-12 col-md-8 offset-md-2">
			<figure class="center">
				<img src="https://s3.amazonaws.com/garybunofsky.com/pass-prototype-1.jpg" alt="tiny-notes-iphone-3" />
			</figure>
		</div>
	</div>
	
	<div class="row mb-10">
		<div class="col-sm-12 col-md-6 offset-md-3">
			<h3 class="lg">Why save the params as cookies?</h3>
			<p class="md">Without cookies, if a user were to revisit the site, the campaign would recieve no attribution. Cookies were used to keep the results intact. Each and every value was stored as a cookie with a default expiration of 30 days.</p>	
		</div>
	</div>
	
	<div class="row mb-6">
		<div class="col-sm-12 col-md-6">
			<h3>User Flow</h3>
			<ol>
				<li>User visits website 💻</li>
				<li>Url params are saved as cookies 🍪</li>
				<li>Cookies values are passed into hidden form fields 🏈</li>
				<li>Campaign params are tracked in Google Analytics 📈</li>
			</ol>
		</div>
	</div>
	
	<hr class="sm mb-8" />
	
	<div class="row mb-12">
		<div class="col-sm-12 col-md-6">
			<p>The motivation to write Pass.js came from the need to analyze refferal traffic for PPC campaigns.</p>
			<%= link_to "View Site", "http://garybunofsky.github.io/pass.js/", class: "btn btn-primary" %>
		</div>
	</div>
	
	<div class="row">
		<div class="col-xs-6 col-sm-6 col-md-6 col-lg-6 mb-6">
			<%= link_to "/portfolio/veronica", class: "card shadow" do %>
				<div class="text-center">
					<p class="mb-0">Previous project</p>
					<h3 class="md">Veronica</h4>
				</div>
			<% end %>
    </div>
		
		<div class="col-xs-6 col-sm-6 col-md-6 col-lg-6 mb-6">
			<%= link_to "/portfolio/tiny-notes", class: "card shadow" do %>
				<div class="text-center">
	      	<p class="mb-0">Next project</p>
					<h3 class="md">Tiny Notes</h4>
				</div>
			<% end %>
		</div>
	</div>
	
</div>